As far as I know, all the events with the same sid in durable_rules require unique ids. You might need to give a different id to the timer event. 

The following example works for me.
```python
from durable.lang import *

with ruleset('VMC'):
    @when_all(m.Cmd == 'On')
    def start_timer(c):
        c.start_timer('my_timer', 5, c.m.id + 1)
        print('my_timer %s' % (c.m.id + 1)) 

    @when_all(timeout('my_timer'))
    def end_timer(c):
        print('Stop')

    @when_start
    def start(host):
        host.post('VMC', {'id': 1, 'sid': 1, 'Cmd': 'On'})

run_all()
```

