@janosroden I encourage you to use `ip2.py` as ip.py was **deprecated** with proper warning in the docstring and it will be removed in **3.0**.

`IPWARE_PRIVATE_IP_PREFIX` and `IPWARE_LOOPBACK_PREFIX` are tested thoroughly, so just copy them into your settings and modify them to your needs.

`IPWARE_META_PRECEDENCE_ORDER` can be passed into the ip2.py version along with few more enhanced feature.  Have a look at  the optional `request_header_order` param.

```python
def get_client_ip(
    request,
    proxy_order='left-most',
    proxy_count=None,
    proxy_trusted_ips=None,
    request_header_order=None,
)
```

@dryice if there are any private ip blocks that are missing from the settings, please send them in for inclusion.

