I finally figured it out. Regarding the djangoRMI is null Error:
Make sure you to load the tags and set them:
```
    var tags = {% djng_current_rmi %};
    my_app.config(function(djangoRMIProvider) {
        djangoRMIProvider.configure(tags);
    });
```

The problem is djng_current_rmi might return null. This happens when the context does not provide a view variable. This in turn happens when you specify your class view like this:
`class MyJSONView(JSONResponseMixin, View)`
instead of using this:
`class MyJSONView(JSONResponseMixin, ContextMixin, View)`

So the documentation is not only poor but also wrong! Please update it, this took me over an hour to figure out.

