```

@new2python Does the updated `forward()` method work for you?

I'm a bit hesitant to add this as a helper method since it's quite easy to implement yourself and users may easily have other things they want to do before forwarding the message, in which case the method is useless.

The same goes for a `reply()` method. I'm not sure we can make it flexible enough to be genuinely useful.

In the shell, it is normal: your `__str__` method uses a translatable field, so when the shell tries to display an object, calling `__str__`, you get that error. You should change your method to this:

```python
def __str__(self):
    return self.safe_translation_getter('title', str(self.pk))
```
This way, if no translation is loaded, the shell will display the id instead of just raising an error.

